H0.text: If ultimate means last, what word means second-to-last. Antepenultimate

H1.text: If ultimate means last, what word means second-to-last. Preultimate

H2.text: If ultimate means last, what word means second-to-last. Proximate

H3.text: If ultimate means last, what word means second-to-last. Penult

A4.text: Penult is a linguistics term for the second-to-last syllable of a word.

A5.text: The main stress falls on the penult in such English words as banána, and Mississíppi, and just about all words ending in -ic such as músic, frántic, and phonétic.
